            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model Card Maintenance on Version Updates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic periodically releases updated Claude model versions with improved capabilities, changed behavior, or shifted safety profiles. Each version update is a potential invalidation of the evaluation results, limitation descriptions, and behavioral claims in existing system cards. A maintenance process that updates the card with every version change — rather than letting the card drift — is the difference between reliable compliance documentation and a liability."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers how to detect when a version update requires card changes, what evaluation work is needed before the card can be re-attested, and how to communicate version changes to customers and regulators who have relied on prior card versions."
          }
        ]
      },
