        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# version_upgrade_notification.py — checks notification obligations before upgrade\n\nimport json\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass UpgradeNotificationPlan:\n    from_model: str\n    to_model: str\n    change_type: str   # \"patch\" | \"minor\" | \"major\" | \"family\"\n    customers_requiring_notice: list[str]\n    regulatory_obligations: list[str]\n    change_ticket_required: bool\n    aiia_update_required: bool\n    red_team_required: bool\n\nCHANGE_TYPE_RULES = {\n    \"patch\": {\n        \"change_ticket\": True,\n        \"aiia_update\": False,\n        \"red_team\": False,\n    },\n    \"minor\": {\n        \"change_ticket\": True,\n        \"aiia_update\": True,\n        \"red_team\": False,\n    },\n    \"major\": {\n        \"change_ticket\": True,\n        \"aiia_update\": True,\n        \"red_team\": True,\n    },\n    \"family\": {\n        \"change_ticket\": True,\n        \"aiia_update\": True,\n        \"red_team\": True,\n    },\n}\n\ndef build_notification_plan(\n    from_model: str,\n    to_model: str,\n    change_type: str,\n    contracts_with_ai_change_clause: list[str],\n    high_risk_eu_ai_act: bool,\n) -> UpgradeNotificationPlan:\n    rules = CHANGE_TYPE_RULES[change_type]\n    regulatory = []\n    if high_risk_eu_ai_act and change_type in (\"major\", \"family\"):\n        regulatory.append(\"EU AI Act: update database registration + tech docs\")\n    if change_type in (\"major\", \"family\"):\n        regulatory.append(\"ISO 42001 Cl. 8.3: update AIIA + change record\")\n    return UpgradeNotificationPlan(\n        from_model=from_model,\n        to_model=to_model,\n        change_type=change_type,\n        customers_requiring_notice=contracts_with_ai_change_clause if change_type != \"patch\" else [],\n        regulatory_obligations=regulatory,\n        change_ticket_required=rules[\"change_ticket\"],\n        aiia_update_required=rules[\"aiia_update\"],\n        red_team_required=rules[\"red_team\"],\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CI/CD Integration for Card Maintenance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Manual card updates are error-prone. Integrate card maintenance checks into the deployment pipeline so that a version upgrade cannot reach production without triggering the required review steps:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/claude-version-upgrade.yml\nname: Claude Model Version Upgrade\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - 'config.py'          # contains CLAUDE_CONFIG with model version\n      - 'system-card.yaml'\n\njobs:\n  model-card-gate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Detect model version change\n        id: version_check\n        run: |\n          OLD=$(git show HEAD:config.py | grep 'model:' | awk '{print $2}' | tr -d '\",')\n          NEW=$(grep 'model:' config.py | awk '{print $2}' | tr -d '\",')\n          echo \"old_model=$OLD\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n          echo \"new_model=$NEW\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n          if [ \"$OLD\" != \"$NEW\" ]; then\n            echo \"version_changed=true\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n          fi\n\n      - name: Verify system card updated\n        if: steps.version_check.outputs.version_changed == 'true'\n        run: |\n          CARD_MODEL=$(python3 -c \"import yaml; c=yaml.safe_load(open('system-card.yaml')); print(c['model_identity']['base_model']['model_id'])\")\n          CONFIG_MODEL=$(grep '\"model\"' config.py | head -1 | awk -F'\"' '{print $4}')\n          if [ \"$CARD_MODEL\" != \"$CONFIG_MODEL\" ]; then\n            echo \"ERROR: config.py model ($CONFIG_MODEL) != system-card.yaml model ($CARD_MODEL)\"\n            echo \"Update the system card before merging this PR.\"\n            exit 1\n          fi\n          echo \"Model versions in sync: $CARD_MODEL\"\n\n      - name: Verify change log entry exists\n        if: steps.version_check.outputs.version_changed == 'true'\n        run: python3 scripts/validate_model_card.py system-card.yaml\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model card maintenance on version updates requires classifying each Anthropic release by its behavioral impact — patch updates need only a version field change, while major model family upgrades require full re-evaluation, red-team re-testing, and potentially customer and regulatory notification. The technical foundation is a version-controlled evaluation suite with a stable checksum that produces comparable results across model versions. Every update produces a structured change log entry documenting what changed, who approved it, and what notifications were sent. CI/CD integration enforces the gate: a PR that bumps the model version in config.py without a matching system card update fails the build before it can reach production."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
